\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Could I ask you what year you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you're a widow now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What was your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 1896.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Yes, I was born in - League Street, Bath Street, Old Street. It's round off of Old Street there. Where the late St Luke's printing works was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know how many years you lived in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - I suppose we used to live there - well - well my other brothers were born there you see, well I suppose about twenty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 All your childhood was spent in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not in that one house, but my brothers previously, yes. Then - we moved to Ironmonger Street, Ironmonger Row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How old do you think you were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well then I was - about - ten to twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So all your early years of childhood were spent locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Local, quite locally, St Luke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know why your family moved out of your first house, did they have a reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Not exactly only we wanted a bigger place, see, because - my mum had seven children, you see, and we were all beginning to grow up, so we had to have a house on our own. And we were in that house thirty years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You said you had six brothers and sisters and you made the seventh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, I had - three brothers, and four sisters and myself, but one of my sisters died when she was a baby. And I've still got three 
sisters and a brother alive, two got killed in the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know how many years there are in between your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - practically - say two years a piece.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And where do you come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I come the third one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So you had a couple of older brothers did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Two older brothers and then you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Two were in the war, one in the Sixth Dragon Guards and one in the Cold stream Guards, and they both got killed in the 1914 war.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And then you had another couple of brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, one more brother and he's still alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And your other sisters were much younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - not much younger, only really - going down two years apiece. My youngest sister was sixty-three on the ninth of 
November, a fortnight ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So there wasn't really that much gap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - well I suppose - dad must have been about twenty-eight. And he died when he was forty-four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Braintree. That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 He was a pianoforte remover. For Nelson Murdoch's in Goswell Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that always his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Always. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 He didn't have any part time jobs or other casual jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, never dear. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that quite a safe sort of job to have at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well it was more or less. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did he have to do any sort of - did he start as a boy and learnt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well when he became - working age, after he left school, I suppose probably he grew up and - mother met him - in London of course. And they were married and - when they married he was - working in the - pianoforte removing trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It's a really skilled sort of job isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I - he was a big man. We're all a big family really, tall you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I've seen this where they get things through these fantastic little windows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear. And if they couldn't get them they should have to help - to go up the staircase.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 He worked in London did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, Go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 well Road. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And presumably he went all over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well much - much about the same age as dad. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did she ever have a job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, she used to go office cleaning - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 of a morning. And me being the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 el - eldest girl - of course I used to have to get the children off - washed and dressed and get them ready for school and then get meself ready. Mum was home from work by then. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's the only job she ever did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Oh yes, that was part - part time job, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know where she came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - local. Local, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's how your father met her in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you would look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 While your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You didn't have to employ anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about your life at home when you were a child, up till when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we were very poor but happy. We had our luxuries mostly - Saturday, Sunday, Monday. Dad used to go to Smithfield market on Saturd
ay, buy a aitch bone of beef. And he'd cut the steaks off the Saturday. Roast for Sunday. In a saucepan for Monday. And - so on, and then - probably on Tuesday mum would make a steak and kidney pudding or pie. And stewed lamb probably Wednesday, but we al
ways finished up on Friday - with a - big currant pudding, or else a pot of boiled rice between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 But you remember eating well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely. Well I don't look too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember how many rooms there were in your house when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Six. Six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Two, two and two and a scullery. At the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So you had a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Kitchen, parlour and four -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Bedrooms upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did anyone besides your parents and brothers and sisters live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, only just our family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, we didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You didn't have any relatives with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You say your mother didn't have to pay anyone for help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Because you were the oldest daughter and able to look after the children for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was your washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mother done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It wasn't sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mother done that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about clothes? Can you remember your mother making any family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No, mother never made no clothes, used to buy our - clothes. But we had a - aunt, she had a public house, funny enough - in Cambridge Heath, and me being like on the big side, what she use - didn't want, mum used to be glad of for me, 
and shoes and various things you know. But we struggled on, we didn't have - really bad life. We was always brought up to know our manners. That's the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would your mother actually mend clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh mother would, yes. Me mother would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember where you' buy clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Yes. We used to - Dolson in City Road which is still there now. And there used to be a shop in - Old Street, by the name of Bridgland. And that's where mum used to - buy various things. 'Cos they 
used to - have cheques and - so much a week. If you had a ten pound cheque you'd pay ten shillings a week. See, to - paid up, then you'd renew it, and so it sort of run out like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And then you could go and get clothes worth this amount?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right, yes, clothes yes. Well I mean a pair of stockings in those days was only two three farthings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How often would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh not too often dear. Well Christmas time yes. Always special Christmas. And we used to wear the tam o'shanta
 hat. With one of those feather bobbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about shoes, did your father ever make shoes or mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no, we - pretty lucky with shoes you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 He didn't ever repair them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No. Out to be repaired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know where you'd buy shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Yes, there used to be - now let me think of the shop - in Bath Street called - Costers. In Bath Street. And that was there for years and years and years. And - they used to have a sale every Monday afternoon. And they used to sel
l oddments, and they used to call 'em a penny left and a ha'penny right. It's true. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Is that where often you would buy shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Always. Well our shoe - boots were only two and eleven. I remember when I - worked in the pub opposite Costers, tha
t was in 1913 I think I started there, and - my best pair of shoes, patent shoes - must have been about ten and eleven which would cost about three pounds something today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about your father, can you ever remember him helping in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well dad, no, 'cos he had to work too late. I mean in those days they used to be out at six and seven in the morning. And never come home probably 'til sometimes nine at night. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So he really didn't have time to help your mother with any cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, definitely, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or washing up or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about making fires, would he ever do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, mum used to do that. Mum used to be up first. Make the fire and make the tea. Our - breakfast of course, w
ash and dress us and - well I used to do that of course when mum was at work when we - got old enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about repairs in the house, or decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh no, the landlord used to do all that. Yes, we never had to pay for it, it was paid by the landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you have to go and tell him if something needed doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, when you paid your rent - you told him - that there was certain things want doing and - then they'd come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was it kept in good repair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 They were quite responsible in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Definitely yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your father ever dress you or undress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, Saturday night was our bathing night, in a - in a big tin - tub, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would he ever tell you stories or read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well he never really had time. See? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever go out with your father alone, without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And he didn't ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh well he - well he would be there. Because we - were always brought up to behave ourself, so there's never no twice telling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You just said you had to look after the younger children while your mother was out, was there anything else you had to do in
 the house when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well, not in the house but what I used to do - I used to go, after school time - I used to go home with a Jewish girl, and help to clean - her mother's place for sixpence. Yes, and that shop was in City Road, name of Lieberman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s. Just before you get to - Buchanan Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well - about twelve. 'Cos my mother brought us up to know how to do housework, and she would stand over us. She used to say plenty of water after first. And the way of the boards, plenty of water after rinse, then slowly dry. And that was her tuition.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did any of your younger brothers and sisters have to do any jobs at all in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only clean - clean the shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that the boys had to do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, mother was very particular about our shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, seven o'clock. Seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we used to help dear ourselves to bed, wash our hands and face and - then go to our bedrooms and - sort of go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd probably help the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
We definitely, oh yes. I remember when my sister, as I tell you, she was sixty - three on the ninth of November, which was a fortnight ago, she was born on
 a Monday morning, and to be truthful - and I'm not ashamed to tell you, I don't suppose my mother had two shillings to bless herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So every extra child one recognised was going to cost more for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right. More money. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember at what age you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - about six. Six years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you share your bedroom or your bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, with my sisters. We had our bedroom. And my brothers had - had their bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you share a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely share a bed. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Where did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Down in the kitchen. Saturday nights mother used to light a big fire, 'cos we used to have a big fire, coal fire then, and - we used to bath in front of the fire, undress, put our nighties on ready for bed see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You always did that regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's - that was routine, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 When would you have clean clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, we used to have clean clothes like - on the Sunday morning we - used to get up, and there was all y
our clean clothes there ready to change. But every other - we used to wear pinafores - then. And every other day more or less going to school we had a clean pinafore. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Where did your family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In the kitchen. 'Cos we had a scullery, and a kitchen you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember any occasions when you'd eat in any other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your mother cook in the scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. More - on the gas stove, but when she used to roast the joint on Sunday - she us
ed to roast it in front of the fire. In front. See? The thing was fixed to the - mantelpiece, you know, and the chain used to drop with a hook, and - it used to be like a clock, get - go so many times one way, and so many times the other, and so it went o
n, with a dish - used to have a - like a drawer to pull out of the stove and used to rest the dish on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I'll bet meat tasted good cooked like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Definitely. Yes, oh yes. We had - we didn't do so bad on it any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you had a gas stove as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Out in the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did that come later, the gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No, it - mother always liked - cook - looking - cooking by the fire, until we - got older, and then - of course - she - got talking to people, they said, I wonder you go t
o that trouble, why don't you bake your food - in the oven, because she had a - oven in those days. See, with the fire. So she did - and she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What time would you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - weekdays was about - half past seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would all the family eat together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Definitely. Definitely, mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did you actually have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh well we had a poor - a very poor breakfast, was bread and butter, jam or marmalade and tea. And Sunday morning we used to get an egg. Always a special - thing at Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would your father be with you for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 More or less. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about midday meals, would you all be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, two o'clock dinner Sunday. And six o'clock tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 During the week would you go home from school to have your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely, no school dinners them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would your father go home as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, he was at work all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What would you have for a midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I told you you see, stew - a stew, stewed st
eak or steak - kidney pudding. Or steak and kidney pie. And - tell you Fridays we had a - poor meal, but it was food. Currant pudding or - rice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's the end of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, that's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well just bread and butter and jam. No - you know, particular - tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Any supper would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Used to have - ha'porth of - chips from the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Nearly every evening you'd have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Big - plateful. Well, my grandma when she was alive, she lived next do
or, and - she used to come in to mum - and they'd have a - two hapenny and ha'porth, fish and - was - which was just - they used to say, get a middle piece of skate, and it was the middle piece of skate for a ha'penny. And a ha'porth of chips, that was tu
ppence. And coming along the - I used to go to the public house and get a pint of porter. Which was the pub I first started working at. It was three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 ha'pence. So they had a good - supper, for three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 pence ha'penny. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about Sunday tea, would you have anything different on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we might have a cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would your mother have baked that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, used to buy it. Buy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your mother or father ever bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, never. No. No. Well it was only tuppence ha'penny a loaf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 For a large one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did she ever make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No bottling fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did she ever make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well you could - get a large jar of mustard pickles for sixpence then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about her own remedies, would she ever make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not in those days, oh no. Well I mean you could go to the doctor for sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And he'd give you something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have a garden at all at the back?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, not a garden dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So you couldn't grow any fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd buy fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely yes, we didn't go short of anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No. Mother never ever brought - it was always fresh food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you keep any livestock at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No, only a pussycat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No hens or rabbits or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember how many times a week you ate meat, by the sound of it you ate meat almost every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, we had steak on - one, two, three - more or less five days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember ever eating tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, never. Never, my mother didn't believe in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was there tinned meat around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I don't think there was, if it was it - I didn't know anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever get any extra meat from people selling rabbits that they'd poached?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. W
e used to go to Whitecross Street, which is in Old Street - and at the top there used to be a stall with rabbits. And he used to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 oasting rabbits, which were the right - stuff to buy. Austin rabbits. Tame rabbits. Oh definitely. They cost about - now 
- oh they cost about a pound. Mm. Now I - if there was - as cheap as that. Well I mean you don't hear of them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you ever remember seeing your mother have less food so that her family could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well no, what we had we shared and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was your father given larger portions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well dad always had a good meal 'cos it was a - had a heavy job didn't he. See, and then when I started work when I first started work - pardon - I started in a factory as a blouse finisher, for half a crown a
 week. And mother used to have two shillings and I used to have sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would your father have a cooked meal in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh always. Always, always. Definitely. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. Definitely no. And I've never eat with your knife like I've seen 'em do here. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what there was or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 We had to have what mother gave us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What would your parents say if you left some food on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well you'll eat it when you're hungry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 She didn't like to see food wasted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or did you have to wait till it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 Oh no, say - would you p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 ass me the salt please, and they used to pass it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Could you ask for second helpings if there was any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 If there was any left. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In a proper way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, your knife - like that you see. Oh definitely - table manners was the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 When we were all finished. Unless you were going anywhere and you said please mother can I leave the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And could you take books and toys to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. Not allowed to read at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you all sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you always have your same places in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. That's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How was the meal served, who would serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well mother would. Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you served in any special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well she'd sort of go round with the potatoes on each pl
ate, and then with the green, cabbage or whatever was next and then with the meat, and gravy, and then we'd - be away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about your younger brothers and sisters, did they sit at the table with you when they were little or did they get fed separately?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, they sit at the table 'cos they used to have a high chair then didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And would one of you help feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, only the baby, my mother used to feed her in her high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 When they were old enough they sat on ordinary chairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs22\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. That's quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember your mother, was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 She was, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 She was an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Yes. She died at sixty-nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And if you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, if you - had any worries but - I don't think I had a lot - to go down to tell her, I'm sure I - I had too much of a good husband.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Your father, was he an easy person to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And he was an affectionate man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you be able to talk things over with your father quite easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 If you were worried about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh no. No. No, you confide in your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh in the proper way. Please mum and dad, and thank you mum and dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 People expected politeness from their children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Definitely. Oh yes. We were always told never to be rude to anybody, we were in trouble - to come and tell the
m and they would thrash it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Definitely. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 As the older sister you were expected to look after them were you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And be sort of kind to them? Did they say you should hit back if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, they used to say take your own - you know, your own part sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You had to learn to be independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What kind of a person do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - we grew up before she died didn't we? See? I was married like - I married while my mother was alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were there certain things they considered were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they point out some things were right, some things were wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Cleanliness and your manners. That was the most important thing. Cleanliness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Your mother would always stress this to you would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - never. Never. No. Neither did mum and dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we'd get a smack and sent to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mother would smack you would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Not dad. No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you ever remember any particular occasion when you got into trouble for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Where, in the house? When my brother and I had an argument - I run upstairs and I just put the boot behind me - and it happened to kick him in the mouth. But I was chased for it. And of course I got punished for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember how you'd feel about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well you'd feel a bit hurt but - my mother wasn't a person that sort of - kept going on about it, you soon forgot it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Once things were over they were finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you say you received your ideas on how to behave from both of your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well mother was more - 'cos we saw more of mum than we did dad because he used to go out early and come home late didn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about birthdays, can you remember that being different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh well we were - always had a little something extra on our birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You had a little present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
That's something I do - like now is birthdays and any - anniversaries. That's two main things, but Christmas I am not all that because it's too }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 commercialised}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859  these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you ever have anyone in to tea on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you'd have some little present from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mother, mm hm. If it's only a sixpence it's a present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you have a birthday cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, couldn't afford it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about Christmas, can you remember any Christmases you spent with your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh we'd always - yes, always every Christmas - we had turkey, always turkey. Oh we used to have a wonderful Christmas, we used to hang our stocking up, get an apple oran orange, and a new penny. And that was your Christmas stocking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you buy presents for your mother and father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Wasn't in the position to buy it. And I had sixpence pocket money, well then - we'll go on to it now - when I was - seventeen - I went round for mother's drink one Sunday 
evening - and the guv'nor asked me would I like to be a barmaid. I thought it was wonderful. I went back and asked mother of course. Well she said how do you feel about it? Well I said I'd rather like it. Anyhow I - went into the trade in 1913, and I neve
r ever looked back, till - four year ago. Seventy-one when I came out the trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about Christmas Day, would you have Christmas pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, Christmas pudding and - oh - up - right up to date Christmas. 'Cos mother belonged to a yearly clu
b. Used to pay so much a week. And then Christmas they'd share out the club. And my grandma used to hold it, hold the club and - she would share out in golden sovereigns. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You can remember that can you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, when I first went behind the bar we used to take golden sovereigns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have any musical instruments in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not 'til late. When I was about - sixteen I suppose, and we had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you play that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I began to play but - of course you know when you're - young you want to get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So you didn't ever give the time to practicing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did anyone sing in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only my husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 But when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you sing as a group family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. I can sing a fairish song now if I'm put to the test.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your parents ever play with you at all, any indoor games?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, we used to - play at hide and seek. My mother'd get her thimble, and she'd we'd have to close our eyes and s
he'd hide it. And then we used to go - and find - and it we were nearer - article she'd say, you're hot, or you're cold. Right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And she'd play that with you would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would they play any games outside the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have any books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, we used to have comics and - different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you take a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mother never allowed us to read the newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would she have one in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 They'd always have a daily paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm hm. That's one thing I do like is the - paper now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Any magazines would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 But you'd have comics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Comics, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or to each other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, they never had time, there were seven os us and there was such a lot to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you ever remember any funerals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only dad's. And of course me mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 But not when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And my little baby I lost. But not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You don't remember seeing any funerals when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only my - grandma and grandpa. And of course my dad and my mother, and the little baby I lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you go to your grandmother's funeral when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, I was too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, well we used to make friends ourself. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You weren't taken out by your mother to visit people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, my mother - had to much to do to ever go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever go shopping with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I used to go and do the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. Used to go myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You can't remember going out with your father for walks by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did he ever take any of the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No dear, none of us. Well he - he didn't have the time I don't - Sunday he was always glad to rest wasn't he. Because they used to work Saturday in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember going on any outings with your parents on Bank Holidays or any other days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh we went to Victoria Park you know on a holiday Monday. Used to be a penny fare didn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd all go would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Penny on the bus. Or on a horse drawn tram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You can remember going on one of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh definitely. They used to change - horses down at Moorgate Street, they used to take the two horses from the front, and bring 'em round - to the back and then they used to go back up that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How far was Victoria Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well it - I don't know if you know - Hackney Road at all. Cambridge Heath. Just through Bishops Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did anything special take place there on a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only roundabouts and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 They'd have a sort of fair would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Ah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that always there on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. Never. Couldn't afford it dear. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not 'til you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we didn't actually. We were too happy at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember how you spent Saturdays when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well - used to help mother with the work, with the housework. And we used to go out to play, after it was all done, washed and dressed and go to play. We used to have a high tea Saturdays. Such as kippers or had dock or something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we have - a cake for tea. I've told you, roast beef for dinner and - all various things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh Sundays yes, we'd wear different clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You had your best clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, our best bits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. We were never allowed to knit. No. That's a very - thing - much against th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 e - well to knit or - sew, unles}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s it was the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s clothes but to - say you - took in - dressmaking, if you done that on a Sunday that was supposed to be right against the rule, from your Sunday school anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What could you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well just - lead a quiet life Sundays, and go to Sunday school after dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your parents go to church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 But you went to a Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, we went to - St Luke's Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you go on any Sunday school outings you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you go to any other activities associated with the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh used to go to the - entertainment, you know - pictures, films.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did the Sunday school run any clubs or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No dear. No. Well of course the - war broke out in 1914 - so you couldn't do a lot then could you, 1918 it finished. So of course that all - went with the wind didn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you in a choir at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you know if the church where you went to Sunday school ran any temperance clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. As a matter of fact - from the school I went to, the day school, I get a - pension now. Don't know if you Cripplegate? Well o
ur school - where went to - Percival school, we never - I never went to a London County Council school, it was private, never paid. See, went to this school, it's still in Old Street, it was Percival school, what they called - St Luke's Percival schools, 
a
nd it came under Cripplegate. And - then - very - we had to march to church Sunday morning. Right? And we was all allowed clothes from there, and the boys had theirs but my dad - my husband went to the same school, and they used to have suits with the Eto
n collars. We used to have a - print dress in - winter - in the summer, and a - this - special coat and all that for winter. Oh yes, we used to have wear the straw hat with a band round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you'd have to go to church on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Every Sunday. An
d once a month we had the band. To march us to church. Well when I was an old age pensioner - Cripplegate come to see me. And - that's where I get three pound five a month from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Because you'd been to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right, Cripplegate. And I receive it here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I've never heard of that before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh well you know now. Yes, they've got my Giro book, they send me a Giro cheque book see and I used to have to go - the first of every month and draw that three pounds five. Well I used to save that for my electric. And different other things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you ever a member of a temperance club, you didn't sign anything when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You didn't belong to any other clubs organised by the church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Now what - other did we used to go to? Where you couldn't drink - where you - sign the pledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you do that when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. I never ever drunk 'til I was - well after I was married, although I was in the public house trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you actually signed the pledge when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was this a sort of Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What would they do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well they just give you little - sermons on what you should do and what you shouldn't do and - what not to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that a Sunday thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, in the week day, Tuesdays. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Any prayers, were you taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you didn't have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well more or less. He was a - Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You remember him talking about the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's quite right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Why do you think he would be a Labour supporter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Don't know. Don't know, I've got no idea. 'Cos my husband was a Conservative so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember your father ever voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, he used to go and vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And what about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 She'd go with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you think she'd vote the same way as he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh more or less, yes, definitely, oh without a doubt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 She'd be a supporter of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In some places at that time people felt they risked losing their job if they voted differently from thei
r employers, do you think your father felt that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, I'm sure he didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 He felt free to vote as he wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No pressure put on him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was your father a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And he didn't ever do any work at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you tell me when your parents weren't doing their work how did they spend their free time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well they'd read the paper. And have a chat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No, she'd go and see her sister. The one that had the pub at Cambridge Heath. And her sisters would come and see her. That's the only thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 My mother wasn't that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 She didn't go out to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, she'd thought too much of her home, no, she thought too much of her home and her children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Your father would get home quite late in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So how many days a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 We didn't - Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So he didn't have much time to go out and enjoy himself either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No dear, no, as I say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember him going to any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And your mother wouldn't either? Did he take part in any sports, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only horse racing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was he interested in racing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well not a lot because you couldn't afford a lot those days, it used to be sixpence, not pounds like today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did he ever go to races?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 But he'd have a little bet would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Little - sixpence on the Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your mother or father ever belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, called - a yearly club. And then they save - well - used to be sixpence a sha
re. Well they'd have five - shares which was a half a crown a week. Well at Christmas time that was five shares, used to work out to about, with your interest you got on your money, used to work out to about seven pounds, well of course seven pound was a 
lot in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It would be a lot to spend on Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right. Yes. Yes, quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You could do quite well out of that couldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they belong to any boot or sick clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or funeral insurance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, only paid insurance, we used to have a Pearl. And Liverpool Victoria.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That was the cover in event of deaths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 All right, we were quite a happy family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You were quite fond of each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was there any one of them you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, I don't think so dear. No, I'm sure not.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Who did you play with as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well a neighbour, one of the neighbour's children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Where would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In the street or up the - in St Luke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s Park. 'Cos where we lived in Ironmonger Street the top was St Luke's Park. That was the church I was married, St Luke's churc
h, and Saturday afternoons they used to have a band there. See? And we used to go up the park and play, or round Bartholomew Square.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So you had quite a lot of open space around you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's quite right dear. With swings in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What games did you play if you were playing in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Skipping rope. Or shuttlecock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you allowed to get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we had to get dirty playing didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Your mother didn't get upset about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well she used to say - say, well you might have kept yourself a bit tidier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you play with quite a large group of children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, just one or two dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you free to play with anyone you wanted to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not exactly, mum used to chose - choose our friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 She'd discourage you from playing with some children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Some, yes. If they wasn't - nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Is that the reason?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. They used to swear and that and mother didn't like that. That's like I don't like here when they swear, it kills me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No dear. No, no, no, not being behind a - barmaid, you never had time. 'Cos I used to work from six in the - we used to open up at six in the morning - 'til twelve at night. And we had two hours off in the afternoon for ou
r rest time. And I used to have a half a day off on a Tuesday, as from one o'clock. Ten shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So as a teenager you didn't have much time to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, ten shillings a week. And then 'course the '14 war was on then, you see, and - m
y husband was invalided out the Army, and he incidentally came in the pub where I was a barmaid. And that's how we - come together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Even though you'd been at the same school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, I knew him. Mm hm. And - from that of course we started going o
ut, and I think that was in about the October, and we were married in the following April. Was married in the same church we used to march to church in Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have any hobbies when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I had too - too much clean
ing and hard work to help mother and - go out cleaning - of a night when I used to go from school to clean for these people. And sometimes Saturday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You said you had a cat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh pussycat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You didn't have any animals of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you collect anything at that time, stamps or matchboxes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No dear, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever go out fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about for walks, would you go out for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh we'd go for walks with our friends, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd go down to the park and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I've got a son goes fishing almost ev - well like - during the season, he's in - they're really mad about it once they start aren't they
 you know on his own boat. So you can tell he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So he does sea fishing does he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
That's quite right dear. He goes to - Dungeness. Dover. And in the summer when he goes for his holidays he goes to Cornwall. And they - he goes to Mavagissey. Oh yes, he's a wonderful fisherman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Fishing's a very popular sport in England apparently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
I said - yes, I say to him - sometimes, you're mad really to go this weather. He said, well when it's raining the fish come up. Yes. Of course he's got all the clothes that he should wear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So he does it properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Definitely. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Does he ever catch anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh does he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 catch? Oh he catches cod and - c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 onger }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 eel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
. 'Course at one time he wanted to bring all the cod he - brought here. I said, no de
ar, don't start it. Then they won't - ex-always expect it. And he knows I like skate, he said well what about fetching a nice wing of skate? I said, no, I said, if the other people saw me having skate and - those on my table, there would be hell to play. 
See, every Monday afternoon I always buy a cake for our table, teatime, I buy a cake. And cut it between the four of us. And I've always got sweets, always got sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It gives a nice feeling amongst people doesn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well of course it does. Oh I like to be that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You were never interested in sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, no, no. Had too much to do apart from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about the theatre, as you got older would you go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh wel
l - yes, when I was courting. I - I was only saying the other day - used to go to Collins's music hall in Islington, my husband and I, used to have the box seat. Three and six. Box seat, three and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Quite a lot wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - we used to com
e out of there, and of course the war was over then see, '14 war, and we used to go into the fish shop, name of Sam Isaacs in - in Upper Street, next to the Islington Empire, and we used to have skate and chips, and - oh butter, both of us, half a crown f
or two. You see what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 People could enjoy themselves for quite a reasonable amount of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about cinemas, did you ever visit a cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, I wasn't a keen - one for going to cinemas. Well I never had time only one night a week did I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about music halls, or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I well you we used to go to the - we used to go to the Collins's or - the Holborn Empire. Or Islington Empire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You had quite a few round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your parents give you any pocket money when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - mother would give us probably three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 pence - or dad would. Which was a lot of money. Because you used to be able to go and get a ha'penny bag of sweets.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would they give this to you regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Is that what you'd mainly spend it on, on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I used to save a penny in the sweet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 stuff club, in a club in the sweet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you ever given any lessons by your parents at home before you went off to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Not before we went off to school, in the evening - we used to be taught to - you know, do sums and different things, but not a lot because mother went to work and dad - went to work see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How old were you when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - five. You weren't allowed to go to school 'til you were five in my days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What were the times, what time did you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Nine 'til twelve. And two - 'til half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well it was a - a church scho
ol. Which - really belonged to St Luke's church, Old Street, because we used to march to church every Sunday morning, but - the first Sunday in every month, we used to march with the band. You see? And that belonged to St Luke's church, 'cos St Luke's chu
rch - and Cripplegate are sort of combined, you see, 'cos Cripplegate is in St Luke's, which moved to Worship Street now, Finsbury Pavement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was this a girls school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, and boys. And we used to be allowed the clothes. In the winter we used to have - slips with woo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 ly - jumpers, with a heavy coat, in the summer we used to have print dresses, straw hats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were these provided?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 By the school. Used to be given to us by the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was it difficult to get into this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, I don
't know, as a little girl I don't think it I was. No, it's all according if your parents - like wanted you to go there because it was a - it was a school where you was brought up in a very - strict way, you know what I mean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, every Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would your parents have to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you think some money was provided?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 The school was endowed with money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It was - provided by - there used to be a drapers shop in Old
 street, which was the name of Bridgmans, and then there was a - big leather shop where they used to go and buy leather and shoe wear, the name of Pedders, well it's all closed down now, and Hughe's Brothers where we got - tools for - doing sort - you kno
w, jobs, and that - they'd - left all the money to - this fund you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you were saying now every person who had been a member of the school when they're older they get this sort of small pension?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear. Soon as you become - a pens
ioner - even a husband and wife can get it. You see, if you've got a husband you can still get it, but I - I didn't know anything about this - for a long time, until somebody said to me, well the Cripplegate money helps you on. I said, what's that? And wh
e
n they told me of course - I made my way next day to Cripplegate in Aldersgate Street it was then. And believe me going up the steps and I thought I was going begging. Honestly, I felt terrible over it. But they were certainly marvellous, they were really
 
lovely. Yes. Well I didn't know. And - then - with in a week - young girls like yourself - used to come - they came and see me, and of course it was all settled. And periodically over the - year - they used to come to see how I was. And Christmas time the
y always brought a hamper. Of groceries and Christmas pudding-box of chocolates and probably a - oh yes, and a box of hankies, always a present from them, nice box of - things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did any of the other members of your family go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, only my two brothe
rs that got killed and myself. But I had the two brothers killed - after they left there you see and their names were outside - I think they're still there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 They were killed in the first war were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In the first world war. I had a - I had a brother killed on the tenth of November. As Armistice was signed on the eleventh. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 The same year, 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You wouldn't believe that was possible really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, but there you are. Mother didn't hear 'til - I think it was about Thursday - when she heard, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 After peace had been signed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Yes. And I was of course in - the bar, well we were just closing about half past two, and somebody come dashing round for me to go home to mother. She'd just got this - letter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd have thought everyone would be safe after that had been signed wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm. They were two big fellows, one was in the Coldstream Guards and one in the Sixth Dragoons. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Wasn't it awful for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I don't think she ever got over it really. And she was allowed ten shillings a week pension for the two of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you near your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was it situated near your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. I - it was up - my - school's in Old street, and I lived up the first
 turning up Bath Street. Where the old Salon used to be on the corner, and then they turned it into the Bank of England didn't they. The printing works. Right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you go to school alone when you first started or did anyone accompany you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, with my - I used to go with my brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about lunch, did you come home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Come home, always come home for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And your brothers did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, oh definitely did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they provide any sort of school dinners where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Never in those days. No, there was no such thing as milk either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Could children get free dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did you think of your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I thought it was wonderful 'cos it was all run on such - strict lines
, you know we were - certainly brought up in the way to know right from wrong. It's a different school altogether to - LCC schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You liked it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely, yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 They were nice. They were quite nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you see anything of the head, did they have a headmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, I think if I can - remember rightly the head teachers name - was Miss Shaw. And - the headmaster's name was Mr Mansfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were the classes separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 They were in different parts of the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right. Well if you was to see it it's a different school altogether, you wouldn't recognise it as a school as you went by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Does this school still exist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I - I don't know 'cos I've been away from there - for such a long time now. 'Cos I was in Whitechapel for twelve years and - I was -

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was it still going on at the time of the second world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh, second world war, oh yes dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 They still wore the uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Yes dear, yes. Matter of fact the other kiddies from the other school - used to call us the Old Street cadgers. Used to call after us when we went along with our clothes on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you mind this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, it's all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were you proud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 All the fun of the fair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did the teachers ever emphasise certain things as important in life, things like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, we were taught - please and thank you, excuse me, and pardon, definitely, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And producing sort of tidy well set out work, things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Oh - oh yes, in every way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Time, oh - yes, otherwise - or else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about ways of speaking, did they ever tell people they should speak in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Certain way, sound your aitches. Oh yes, definitely, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 If you did something teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - if we were naughty they used to bring us out and stand us in the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You can remember occasions where this happened to girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they have any other ways of punishing the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, those days if you were very naughty they used to cane you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was this rare in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Very rare. Very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What sort of offences would they have to be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - if you were fighting one another I suppose, and - it would happen more to the boys than it would to the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were your parents interested in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, they were always particular with what - when
 we used to have the exams, if we passed or not. But my eye, we used to pass - arithmetic and - oh dear - scripture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they ever get the chance to go to the school at all to talk to the teachers about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 People didn't do that so much in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not - not in those days, not like they do today. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever have an open day where they could come and see your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not any plays and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. Definitely no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they used to ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh yes, we used to tell them what we did. But - mother say, well what have you been doing this morning? We'd have drill. We'd have skipping, you know, to keep your limbs exercised.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you do that in a hall or outside?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In a hall. Drilling and - skipping. Our playground used to be at the top of the school, not down in the ground out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd have to go upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that just the girls up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, girls and boys. 'Course there's a big hoarding right round of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You played up the top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right. And that is - if it's still there it's still - opposite the old - St Luke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s printing works where they - built the Bank of England. But that's all changed
 now 'cos it's all new flats built there. And shops underneath, such as Littlewood}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s and - is it Littlewood}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s or - Marks and Spencer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s and - oh well, if you went round there now I mean even - I've been in here six or seven months, it's all changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did most of the other children at your school come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Definitely, they were all - you know, what shall I say - not the fighting mind like some of 'em do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were there any very poor children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we were all poor in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember any who were poorer than others, I suppose the children weren't that badly dressed because they got a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we were allowed the shoes from our school, but of course the other schools they weren't. It's only our - our school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So most of the children would be quite well dressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely, oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So really one was lucky to be able to go to a school like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No go there. Mm hm. You had to have a sort of certain appearance I suppose with mother - took you to be - listed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember seeing children who went to the local board schools who weren't as well dressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, oh definitely, without doubt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did the teachers ever single out any children for different treatment than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No, there was never no favourites. Never no favourites. Me being big and tall I used to be what they called the monitor. 'Cos in those days we had gas lights. Not electric light like we d
o now. And - used to have to go round the classes with the cane and pull the chain - to light the electric light. I was the monitor 'cos of being the tallest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Were there any gangs or groups in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No such thing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember there being any children who were ever left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No, I don't think so, we used to go once a year - to Walton-on-the-Naze. Oh yes. Yes. And - we used to pay a shilling which was a penny a week over a year, you know, they could - and when we got there we used to have a silver three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 penny bit given us - and a - pork pie. Every year. Walton-on-the-Naze, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever go on to any other school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. Only there. Left there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you have liked to have stayed any longer if you'd had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, I was always itchy fingers, wanted to get to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you do any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, I used to go part time - cleaning for people to help my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have any regrets about your education looking back on it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, I can still - reckon up and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You were lucky, you went to a good school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, oh no, I've got no regrets dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh I'm sure. I mean I've been to - different places, you know, the Co-op rooms and the Savoy Hotel }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 to dinners and - dinners, and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 mean you've got to be - sort of - know how to speak, and behave, and dress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 The jobs you had while you were still at school, you said you went and did a bit of cleaning at somebody's shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well that - that was after - school hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How much did you earn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Sixpence a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I used to perhaps to do - two
 or three lots of cleaning for mother. But Friday night always was some Jewish people in City Road, the name of Lieberman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s. And I used to get sixpence, and - used to take it home to mother, which was a help, 'cos we'd get a - quarter of a pound of butter and a loaf and - all that, for less than sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you work on Saturday and Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Just a couple of hours after school each day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. No, not each day. It's all according if they wanted me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would it be a couple of times a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear. If a neighbour wanted me to clean her stairs down - see, I used to go and do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd do a bit for other people if there were other jobs around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. If - yes, mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And they'd all pay roughly the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you like the people where you worked at Lieberman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh they were Jewish people, they were quite nice. I've got a daughter-in-law and she's Jewish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You got on well with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you feel about doing cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 All right. I would still do it here if I had good legs to help 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You quite liked the idea of earning a bit of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did having this job alter your attitude to going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. Not in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you do anything else, in between when you left school before you went into the bar, did you do another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, I used to - oh well - when I started work, I started work at Grimes and Curtiss's in Banner Street. That was down 
Bunhill Row, finishing blouses, you know, finishing off blouses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 With a machine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, hand. For a half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that a full time job, your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Half a crown a week. And I used to give mother two shillings and have sixpence for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well advertised.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You saw it advertised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Had blouse finishers and - wanted and I went after it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What exactly did you have to do in the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well if they give you a - pile of blouses you had to finish 'em. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they show you, were you shown how to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well when I first went there, yes. But of course it's all done by machinery now. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 From eight 'til seven. Eight 'til seven at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Twelve o'clock Saturday. Eight 'til twelve. But not Sunday of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Any half days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, not from in the factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about holidays, did you get any paid holidays while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not in those days, there's no such dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you think that was quite a fair wage at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well in those days a half a crown was a lot of money. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You gave most of that to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Two shillings and I had sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What would she use it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 For the home, in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you get on with the people in the blouse factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh, quite all right, I was always quite - like I am here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was it a small firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, quite a big firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you know the employer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, not at all dear, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd just have a manageress or a foreman or someone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Forelady. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you feel about that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 All right, quite liked it. And I went on with that until I - was eighteen, no, seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Why did you decide to change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well I'll tell you how that was. One Sunday evening - when I was seventeen my mother said to me, will you go and get my evening stout? Beer it was. And I went round to this pub, and I got mother a pint of porter, which was three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
ha'ppence. When I was - being served the guv'nor served me, and he said - now how would you like to come and work for me? I said, all right, I would love, I said, I would like it, I said, but I'll have to ask mum first. So 
I went back and asked my mother. She said, well if you - think you'd like it - you do it. And I went back and told him and I started on the Sunday morning. And that was in - 19 - 18. No. 1913. 1913, 'cos I was there - I was there during the war. That's ri
ght. 1913. And - so I was there 'til after the first world war, went right through with it. And - used to have a half a day off on Tuesdays from one o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What were your hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Six - six in the morning 'til twelve at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What would you be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, you'd be - the pub would be open, it was opened at six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Open for serving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
All day long dear. That's right, that's from six in the morning 'til half past twelve. Pardon. But Saturday was six o'clock 'til twelve at night, because you broke into Sunday if you went - the other half hour. That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well we used to open, on Sunday we used to open - from one 'til three. And from - Seven 'til eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Ten shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So that's quite a rise from when you were finishing blouses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Yes. Well of course - I did - sort of twice the time work didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What exactly did you have to do when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In the bar? Well clean the shelf, do th
e cabinet, and - clean any glasses that were left from o - from over night, which were but we all used to clear up you see. And - then serve. 'Cos customers used to come in at six o'clock in the morning, for what they called a pennorth and ha'porth.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well a pennorth and happorth was a pennorth of rum and haporth of milk. And they used to tip down and off they'd go, men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That would sort of be their breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, call it what you like really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What sort of trade would there be then very early in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Very - very fair. Very fair, well then it would go on during the day. And they'd come in for a pint of - mild, which was tuppence. Pint of ale. Which was tuppence. And then - you'd get the mothers coming f
rom shopping. They more or less all used to wear shawls in those days. And if there was three of 'em, they'd ask - for three stouts, which was three half a pints for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 pence ha'penny. Or else they'd have a - half a quart and three out. Well a half a qua
rt and three out - was three glasses, and a half a quart measure which held - six drops - three drops of whisky. Then they'd help themselves. Yes. That was the measure of three drops, for three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 pence ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did people buy many spirits in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh yes, they did go on then just as they do now. 'Cos we had - quite a big printing family that used to - use our pub, and - they used to drink Guinesses which were three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 pence ha'penny each. And every night they would take a dozen home for three and six. But now you can't get two for three and six.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What were people like in pubs in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Quite nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was there much drunkenness would you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well yes, there was more or less. They used to drink - it seemed to me more in tho
se days. Although the boys and girls today - drink more because they get the money but they drink heavier drinks. Such as vodka and coke and vodka and lime and - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was there a special day when you were most busy, pay day or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Used
 to come - Friday night. Saturday and Sunday. But you'd only just get your running trade all the week. Then we used to do - dinner of a day. Cut from joint and two veg for seven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you help do that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, that was no - no - that's right. Just in the bar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You enjoyed this job did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
I loved it. I loved it, I enjoyed every moment of it. I would - done it 'til I was seventy-one. 'Cos after I retired from Whitechapel where I had my own pub - in 1952, see I knew - knew a l
ot of publicans, and they used to say - if they were short handed - would - could you come and help us, you know, and I used to go and help 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you - remember any particular stories, anything interesting that happened in the bar, anything amusing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh well, we used to have - used to have little sing-songs you know weekend. But - the last publican I worked for had a tragic death. I don't know if you want me to tell you this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Is that when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember anything about when you were young?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Nothing - exciting like that, just went on a normal life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would they have any sort of singing or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, we used to have sing-songs in the bar. We never ever thought of a piano then. No, not like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That came later, pianos in pubs did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 When do you think they came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh about - 1930.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh much later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would it be mostly men at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh no, they used to bring their wives out wi
th them. Mm. And they'd call in from work. And their wives would come in and meet them later, they knew where to find them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever see cases where you think people sort of really spent all their wages drinking and couldn't afford it, should have
 been taking it home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Very often, very often. Very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did people have to pay for everything they had in your pub when you were a girl or could they put it on a slate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well no, we used to say, the slate's broken. Sorry but the slate is br
oken. That's a thing I don't believe in. Because you don't - you don't only lose your money, you lose your custom 'cos they stop out because they can't pay, so you lose your money and you lose your custom. Like when I was in Whitechapel, I used to have th
e
 dockers come over from the London hospital, Lil would you change me a cheque? I used to say, well - what did you want to drink until you go and change it yourself? We want a glass of bitter, well all right, I'll buy you that one, so it was better for me 
to buy them a sixpenny bitter than to lose a pound - wasn't it? Mm. And their future trade. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You say you really enjoyed it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Every moment, dear, I'd still do it again if I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did your parents feel about you working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh all right. My mother knew that I was - getting on all right and that you know. You got a half a day off on a Tuesday from one o'clock. And then - and then I met my husband, 'cos he went to my school. And - he came in one day after he'd been dischar
ged from the Army, and as from that we carried on like, and we were married in 1919 and we used to go to Collins's Empire Islington, for a box seat for three and six. And Sam Isaacs for a fish supper for half a crown. So we both had a night out for - six 
shillings, and my husband was a tailor cutter, so he had a good job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 He'd been apprenticed had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, been apprenticed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Since the first world war, did you work after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh always, I never - wouldn't stop work. As a 
matter of fact after I had my last little boy I went back in the bar after he was three weeks old, because the guv'nor sent for me and I went back and my mother - used to look after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And then later on you had a pub of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That was later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
In 1940. That was when the last war broke out. And - was there right 'til 1952. See? Right through, never shut the pub one night, not for air r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 ids or - just took a chance. Then one night we were sleep in the cellar, they dropped a bomb o
n the London Hospital, blew the front of the pub in. And - then of a night I always insisted upon having a - glass clock put on the counter, with the glasses stood upside down, then in the morning they was all done, brush and put underneath. And this blas
t this night when it blew the front of the pub in, all the glasses were on there and it never shifted one. Well there you are, always remember that, on a Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, definitely no dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 This really suited you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That was lucky then that you went along there really wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Because you might not have done it otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You didn't ever belong to any trade union or anything like that or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No. N}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551116\charrsid16190859 o, no. No, only the Licensed Victuall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 ers Association, which you had to belong to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In case - anything went wrong, then you could go to them for - thrash it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do most publicans belong to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Protection Association.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you feel at that time that employers and workers had got the same interests or was there a lot of difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh I don't know, everybody seemed to - I - you seemed to be interested in their work
. And I - didn't work for many guv'nors because I was so long at - the jobs before I had my own place in Whitechapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Some people say that in those days there was a great difference between trained craftsmen and other workers, would you ever notice th
at being in a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well - yes, print - printer - a printer that was in the print, well of course he earnt a hell of a lot of money, you see. And well there'd be that little bit of class distinction, he'd use the saloon bar, and the others would use the public bar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Does that apply to any other craftsmen of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well perhaps - what can I say - all different trades you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So saloon bars at that time were often sort of unskilled type of workers,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's - skilled types, skilled type of - saloon, and the unskilled use the public. Mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And they'd pay a bit more would they in the saloon bar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - yes, you always paid a bit more. Because you had that better service. Oh yes. And they had a - different kind of glass, th
ey'd have a stemmed glass for their beer. See? And a stemmed glass for their scotch. Where in the public bar they would have just a little - glass.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you think once you started full time work this changed your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, not in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about your home life after you'd left school, you went on living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Until you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, I was married when I was twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Once you'd started work did this change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, not at - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well as a matter of fact when I got married I lived in mother's house. So we was all one - happy family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did your brothers and sisters think of you working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
All right. Well they went to work because - the two elder brothers - of course they were killed in the war wasn't they, so we never had them, well then my sister was two years younger so they used to go two years, two years and two years and they gr
adually went out to work themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you spend your Sundays and differently, what age did you stop doing to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well when I worked at the - pub. Well more or less when I - left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You didn't go on going to church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No. You can still be a Christian without going to church. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you take any interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - I like politics, I like religion, but I never talk on it. I never talk on those two items, because it causes arguments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You like to keep your opinion to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you belong to a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, not any kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or do any work for any political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you spend your spare time, what would you din the evenings you had off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well - when I was single I used to go and help mother with - the work didn't I, washing day would be to - hang the washing up and when it was dry take it down and do the mangling and ironing and - different bits of
 housework in the house, oh there was always plenty to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So there wasn't much time for going out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No. Even when I was seventeen I used to have to say please mother can I go out tonight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever go out in the evenings when you weren't working? Did you ever have an evening off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Tuesday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you go out that evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, go to the film.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You'd go with other friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was anyone of your age working in the bar with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Another - woman worked in the bar with - with me. Think she was a bit old.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you get to know any new friends when you worked at the blouse factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I was never a girl - I was friendly with 'em at work. But after that - like - when we were marr
ied, we only had our own - family, and our own company. We never made no - friends of - but if we went out to have a drink when we saw people we would say good evening and how are you and things like that, all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You kept your social and your private life absolutely to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right, in our family. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you have any special friends at this time, or had you met your future husband by this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 By about 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right, dear, he was invalided out the Army. Through - in the arm, but he looked all right physically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you meet him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 He came into the - he didn't drink, and he came into the bar with - another one of his old school friends and I always remember he had a }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3632836\charrsid16190859 shanty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 . After that he used t
o come in and out, and we would be talking about - school, and - started going out in the November and we were married in the - April.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Where would you go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - Collins's or the Islington Empire. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Your parents expected to know where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh definitely. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they meet your friends? Would you be able to take friends home with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh I used to take my young man home. And any of my friends I had before I had my young man. My husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And your parents approved of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would you have to be home by a certain time at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Always. Yes, in those days always by half past nine to ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Quite early really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, well that was the rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh yes. Yes. Used to have policemen on point duty at every corner, more or less. Nearly on every corner there used to be a point - what they called a point policeman point duty. Difficult to see one today. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did you think of the policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Very nice. As a matter of fact in those days when I first started behind the bar - which was in Bath Street at the Jolly Anglers - Inspector Doyle from Shepherdess Walk used to come in, with his 
- Sergeant, and one day he asked me would I go - out and sell flags for him, his wife, as she'd been taken ill - for the Royal Northern Hospital, Hollyway Road. And I went out - with the flags and I stood outside the Angel Tube. Always remember that. And 
I'm not bragging but I - my box was the most money. Mm hm. Very nice gentleman, he came in and thanked me, Inspector Doyle that was from Shepherdess Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your mother ever threaten you when you were naughty and say I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No, she'd thrash it out herself. So - well we never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So you were never frightened of policemen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. We never done anything really bad, because we was brought up in a different way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 The policeman would be regarded as a friend really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How do you think the police treated people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well - if a policeman saw - saw two little boys doing anything they shouldn't do, he'd box their ears. And say, now run along home? I'll - or else, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever see them dealing with drunk people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh yes. If there was anybody drunk - in those days - we used to phone a police, Shepherdess Walk, and they'd fetch down a - like a barrow - and - it used to be covered over with brown canvass,
 like a hood, and they used to put 'em on that, strap 'em over and take 'em away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 This was if they'd absolutely passed out was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did that happen very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - not too often, but it did happen. I mean if a man went out with a 
shilling in those days, shilling - he could have twelve half a pints or six pints couldn't he. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was your home rented at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did you feel about the landlord, did you ever see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, 'cos we used to go and pay the rent. 'Cos it come under St. Bar - St. Bartholomew's Hospital.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Is that where you rented the property from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, and - the rent collector used to come from there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So really it wasn't an individual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It was St Bartholomew}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3632836\charrsid16190859 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 s Trust of some sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. That's quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they own a lot of property round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh quite a fair bit, yes. Yes, quite -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 A whole sort of street and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. Mm. There was one part called Bartholomew Square.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you ever remember feeling your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh well they did. They did, very much. Quite true they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Some times were better than others were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Your father wasn't actually out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
No, but more or less all the same all the time as I told you, we used to finish up with a currant pudding or a pot of rice on Friday 'til dad got paid. But apart from that we lived all right. 'Cos mum - mother did a bit of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 As long as the family had a regular wage coming in you could manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right. That's - that's quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It was just unemployed periods where families had great difficulties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was your father ever ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well - yes, he finished up dying with - with consum - TB, consumption. He was in and out of Brompton. He died at forty-four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was this when he still had young children to support?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I suppose my - what age was I? Oh yes, of course, I mean I was only about seventeen. Eighteen when dad died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So there was still quite a few younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 But you all helped did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Oh yes. I remember going to - what they used to call the Red House there in - Clerkenwell Road to ask for help for mother, and they gave me two shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 A gift. Gift. And - and that was for - wait a minute - that was four - five - five os us and mum, to help with five of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Who was that, who actually were the people you went to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Why the - what they used to call the Red House, just along in Clerkenwell Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What was that like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 More or less like a - Town Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's like a sort of Board of Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did they make a fuss about giving the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh they did. I -
 they said, how many rooms have you got, and I told them where we slept. Well they said you could do without that room, your brother could sleep - in - the kitchen. Ah, I said, but you - came round and you issued a notice - that should you - we should not
 eat, sleep and drink in one room. So they cut that out right away didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 So that's all they gave you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Two shillings dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you only go that one time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It's not really worth going back again is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What was their attitude though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh - quite hard to get the two - two shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 How did you feel about going there, did it worry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I didn't mind, I was quite willing to go for mother. No, I was always the speaker of the family. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 When there was someone in the district who people disapproved of can you remember there being any special in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You don't remember hearing the expression rough music?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Where people would bang tin cans and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no, no, no. Quite a respectable turning we lived in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups. Before 1918 would you say some people belonged to one group-and some to another,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, they were more or less all the same. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You don't think there were any sort definite differences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Which class or group do you think you'd say your family belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I should say we were a second class family. We weren't po - top, and we wasn't - the roughs, that we were middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You think there were some people who you would refer to as rough, would they be poorer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well they were more rougher and they were brought up rough weren't they. Swear and that. That's one thing I do detest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would that be through lack of money do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, through bad temper and hearing it in their own homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And there were another group who had a lot more money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 And you'd put yourself in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's quite right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember ever being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, we were always - brought up the same way. Good morning, good evening or good night. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever have to curtsey to anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, no, no, no. No. No dear, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever have to call anybody sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Only your guv'nor and missus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Was that how you'd refer to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well that was the rule wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember people ever calling your mother and father sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No. No, just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about in shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Probably - what would you like madam, if you serve - like I would say to my custome
rs, good morning sir, what would you like? Morning Mrs - whoever she was. That's right. What would you like? Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 In your part of London who do you think were considered the most important people at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I don't - remember anybody being important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Like clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh well they were weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Anybody else like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What would the doctors be thought of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, as a - as a doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would he be considered quite an important member of the community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
If you saw him - if you saw him out you used to say - good morning - Doctor - oh I forget - Glyn, or whatever it was. He would say good morning. Matter of fact my last doctor that I went to before I come here - he used to say to me, good morning Sar
ah, and take care of yourself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about teachers, what were they like, would they be considered important at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh no, not no more important than they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about shopkeepers, who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well the
y - they'd be - well they were open early like we were, they were open here at six - seven in the morning 'til eight at night so they never had much time to spend in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about teachers, do you know if they mixed with each other or would they mix with poorer people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, they mix - they mixed with each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What about employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh they were - they were sort of - on their own you know, they used to go out to lunch and that, they never used to go home to lunch.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You didn't find these groups mixed that easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 People kept in their own social groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What kind of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well like we do today, here and there. But more people went to church in those days than they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you ever know anyone who went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, we used to go to the - the Belisha mission, in City Road. A Mission.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 It's still there isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes. And we used to go there to - film shows and all that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Would different kind of people go to the chapels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Yes, they were - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What way do you think they were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well I can't tell you that, I mean I never mixed with 'em so I can't tell you. How's the time going on, mustn't be too late down. That's
 been like that for a long time. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Where you lived did most of the people in the workers have the same standard of living as you and your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes. Yes, they were quite nice neighbours, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did you know any poor families anywhere around you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh quite a lot. Oh quite a few poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Who you could look at and say they definitely you know they were a poor family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well, their mums and dads - used to go to the pub and spend more than they could afford. And that's why. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You said that you knew some people were regarded as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Oh yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You say you came from a respectable home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 I say I did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Did your mother and father have the same sort of attitude to people in any of these different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No, they were just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 What did your mother think of people who were rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 My mother used to say - if you go out to play, don't play with so and so, just keep yourselves to yourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Was it possible at that time do you think to move from one group to another? Was it possible for those who were sort of rougher families to sort of mix with the more respectable ones?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 No dear, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 You sort of kept yourself to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Well only me own husband. They used to say he - you know, the neighbours used to say - what a lovely gentleman he is. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 Why do you think they said that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 
Well because he was always respectable, always carried his umbrella and paper under his arm and - say good morning, good evening, and - that's it. Never pass anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5732953 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's what people would refer to as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6831152 W  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12325872\charrsid16190859 That's right dear, mm hm.
\par }}